# Infra hygiene

- **One image per service**; avoid fat multi-app containers.
- Compose defaults should honour **Phase 1 minimal stack** (`infrastructure/docker/docker-compose.yml`): MongoDB + Redis + gateway—use profiles/overrides for Kafka/Rabbit/obs stacks.
- Never bake literal secrets inside images—load via Compose env vars, swarm/k8s secrets, or VPS secret manager equivalents.
- When editing Compose, document how profiles map to roadmap phases (`docs/ROADMAP.md`) in the PR description/README delta when behaviour changes materially.
